## Code Style Rules — Always follow these

### General
- Always use TypeScript. Never use any — use unknown and narrow it.
- Always use named exports for components, default exports for pages.
- Always add "use client" at the top of client components.
- Server components are default — only add "use client" when needed.
- Never use var — always const or let.
- Always handle errors — never leave unhandled promise rejections.
- Always use optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??) where appropriate.

### Components
- Always use shadcn/ui components from @/components/ui — never build from scratch.
- Component files: PascalCase (e.g. ProductCard.tsx)
- One component per file unless tiny sub-components.
- Props interfaces defined at the top of the file with explicit types.
- Never inline style — always Tailwind classes.
- Use cn() from @/lib/utils for conditional class names.

### API Routes
- Every API route must check authentication first using Supabase server client.
- Return 401 if no session — never proceed without auth check.
- Always wrap in try/catch — never let errors bubble up unhandled.
- Always return NextResponse.json() — never plain Response.
- Use proper HTTP status codes: 200, 201, 400, 401, 402, 403, 404, 429, 500.
- Never expose stack traces in responses — log them server-side only.
- Structure: auth check → input validation → business logic → return response.

### Supabase
- Browser client (client.ts): use in "use client" components only.
- Server client (server.ts): use in Server Components, API routes, middleware.
- Never use the service_role key client-side — server only.
- Always use RLS — never bypass it with service_role in user-facing routes.
- Table names are always snake_case and plural.
- Always handle Supabase errors: const { data, error } = await supabase... then check error.

### Environment Variables
- Public (safe for client): prefix NEXT_PUBLIC_
- Private (server only): no prefix — never access in client components
- Public vars: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
- Private vars: SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, HEYGEN_API_KEY, META_APP_ID, META_APP_SECRET, STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET, CRON_SECRET

