## Database Schema — Know these tables

### profiles
id (uuid PK → auth.users), full_name, avatar_url, plan (default: starter),
credits_remaining (default: 30), ai_credits_remaining (default: 10),
onboarding_complete (default: false), created_at

### instagram_accounts
id, user_id → profiles, ig_user_id (unique), ig_username, ig_name,
profile_pic_url, followers_count, access_token, token_expires_at,
is_active (default: true), connected_at

### products
id, user_id → profiles, name (not null), description, price, url,
usp (text[]), images (text[]), niche, tone, is_active, created_at

### content_generations
id, user_id → profiles, product_id → products,
type (carousel | hook_demo | ugc_reel | static_post),
status (pending | generating | ready | failed),
output (jsonb), caption, hashtags (text[]), credits_used, created_at

### scheduled_posts
id, user_id → profiles, generation_id → content_generations,
ig_account_id → instagram_accounts, scheduled_for (timestamptz),
status (queued | publishing | published | failed),
ig_post_id, published_at

### post_analytics
id, post_id → scheduled_posts, views, likes, saves,
comments, profile_visits, fetched_at

### subscriptions
id, user_id → profiles, stripe_customer_id (unique),
stripe_subscription_id (unique), plan, status, current_period_end, updated_at

### credits_log
id, user_id → profiles, action, credits_delta (int, negative = spend),
balance_after, generation_id (nullable), created_at

