## Key Business Logic Rules

### Credit system
- Always check credits BEFORE calling any AI API.
- Use checkAndDeductCredits() from @/lib/credits.ts.
- Return 402 { error: "insufficient_credits", credits_remaining: X } if not enough.
- Always log every deduction to credits_log table.

### Instagram publishing
- Only use Meta Graph API — never use third-party posting libraries.
- Always refresh token if within 7 days of expiry before any API call.
- Handle 429 rate limit with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s).
- Only publish via official Graph API — never simulate or mock publishing.

### Content generation
- Carousel: GPT-4o for script + DALL-E 3 for images.
- Hook+Demo video: GPT-4o for script + HeyGen API for video render.
- Always generate 5 variants per request — only deduct 1 credit total.
- Save every generation to content_generations table with status tracking.
- Poll HeyGen video status — never block waiting for it synchronously.

### Security rules (non-negotiable)
- Every /api/* route: check auth session first, return 401 if none.
- Every Supabase query: use authenticated client, never service_role for user data.
- Rate limit all generation routes: 10 req/min per user.
- Rate limit publish routes: 5 req/min per user.
- Never log access tokens or API keys.
- Never return raw error stack traces in API responses.

